"Spagnoli B., Planton S., Déqué M., Mestre O., Moisselin J.-M.","Detecting climate change at a regional scale: The case of France",2002,"Geophysical Research Letters","29","10",,"90","1",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0037095806&partnerID=40&md5=b09795910acd68775c87f9b83e245a91","Centre Natl. de Rec. Meteorologiques, 42 avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France","Spagnoli, B., Centre Natl. de Rec. Meteorologiques, 42 avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France; Planton, S., Centre Natl. de Rec. Meteorologiques, 42 avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France; Déqué, M., Centre Natl. de Rec. Meteorologiques, 42 avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France; Mestre, O., Centre Natl. de Rec. Meteorologiques, 42 avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France; Moisselin, J.-M., Centre Natl. de Rec. Meteorologiques, 42 avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France","An optimal detection method, already used for global climate change detection, is applied to regional anthropogenic climate change detection, in the particular case of France. This case was chosen for the availability of high quality, statistically homogenized near-surface temperature observations on one hand, and high-resolution climate simulations over this region on the other hand. The detection is conducted on centered patterns, in order to only focus on pattern similarities between observations and model predictions. Detection is successful for 30-year trends of summer minimal daily temperatures at a 90% confidence level, while it failed on summer maximal daily and winter temperatures. This partial success is very encouraging as it shows for the first time the detection of a climate change signal at the regional scale which resembles the one computed by a regional climate model.",,"Climate change; Computer simulation; Signal detection; Regional scales; Geophysics; climate change; mapping; regional climate; France",,,,,,"Barnett, T.P., Hasselmann, K., Chelliah, M., Delworth, T., Hegerl, G., Jones, P., Rasmussen, E., Tett, S., Detection and attribution of climate change: A status report (1999) Bull. Am. Met. Soc, 12, pp. 2631-2659; Déqué, M., Piedelièvre, J.-P., High resolution climate simulation over Europe (1995) Clim. Dyn, 11, pp. 321-339; Hasselmann, K., Optimal fingerprints for the detection of time-dependent climate change (1993) J. Clim, 6, pp. 1957-1971; Hegerl, G.C., von Storch, H., Hasselmann, K., Santer, B., Cubasch, U., Jones, P., Detecting greenhouse-gas-induced climate change with an optimal fingerprint method (1996) J. Clim, 9, pp. 2281-2306; Hegerl, G.C., Hasselmann, K., Cubasch, U., Mitchell, J., Roeckner, E., Voss, R., Waszkewitz, J., Detection and attribution of climate change: Multi-fingerprint detection and attribution of greenhouse-gas and aerosol forced climate change (1997) Clim. Dyn, 13, pp. 613-634; Mestre, O., (2000) Méthodes statistiques pour l'homogénéisation de longues séries climatiques, , Ph.D Thesis, 229 pp., Université Paul Sabatier, Toulouse, September (in french); Mestre, O., Caussinus, H., A new correction model for homogenisation of long instrumental data series (2001) Detecting and Modeling Regional Climate Change and Associated Impacts, pp. 13-20. , edited by M. Brunet and D. López, Springer-Verlag, New York; Mitchell, J.F.B., Karoly, D.J., Detection of climate change and attribution of causes (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis, pp. 695-738. , edited by Houghton et al., Cambridge University Press; Penner, J.-E., Chuang, C., Grant, K., Climate forcing by carbonaceous and sulfate aerosols (1998) Clim. Dyn, 14, pp. 551-839; Royer, J.-F., Cariolle, D., Chauvin, F., Dqu, M., Douville, H., Planton, S., Rascol, A., Valcke, S., Simulation des changements climatiques au cours du 2 lime sicle incluant l'ozone stratosphrique (2001) Compterendus de l'Acadmie des Sciences, , in press; Stott, P.A., Tett, S., Jones, G., Allen, M., Ingram, W., Mitchell, J., Attribution of twentieth century temperature change to natural and anthropogenic causes (2001) Clim. Dyn, 17, pp. 1-21; Tett, S.F.B., Stott, P., Allen, M., Ingram, W., Mitchell, J., Causes of twentieth century temperature change (1999) Nature, 399, pp. 569-572","Spagnoli, B.; Centre Natl. de Rec. Meteorologiques, 42 avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France; email: bruno.spagnoli@cnrm.meteo.fr",,,,,,,,00948276,,GPRLA,,"English","Geophys. Res. Lett.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0037095806
